<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1925-03-03T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1925-03-03T10:00:00-05:00" n="297" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d297">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">721.2315/179: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Morgan</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Rio
                                            de Janeiro</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-03-03T12:00:00-03:00"><hi rend="italic">March 3,
                                            1925—noon.</hi></date><lb/>[Received March 3—11
                                    a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>21. Your telegram number 17, March 2, 2 p.m. was communicated to the
                                Minister for Foreign Affairs this morning. Foreign Office on reading
                                telegram considers Grade’s instructions already adequate.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Morgan</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>